      SuccessfulImageListener getSuccessfulImageListener()
      Returns image listener that will obtain images from the successful scan.

    • Method Detail

      • getSuccessfulImageListener

        @Nullable
SuccessfulImageListener getSuccessfulImageListener()
        Returns image listener that will obtain images from the successful scan. Successful image was used to recognize the item.
        Returns:
        image listener that will obtain images from the successful scan.

      • setSuccessfulImageListener

        void setSuccessfulImageListener(@Nullable
                                SuccessfulImageListener successfulImageListener)
        Sets implementation of SuccessfulImageListener interface that will obtain images from the successful scan. SuccessfulImageListener will receive image when recognition process has successfully scanned an item and has a successful scan image to return.
        Parameters:
        successfulImageListener - Implementation of image listener or null to clear listener that has been set previously.
